				<p style="margin: 28px 0 16px; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;">↓ Three revenue streams flow from these 95 bookings</p>

				<div class="card-grid card-grid-3" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
					<div class="cs-card" style="border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);">
						<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--accent-strong); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 10px;">Option A · Moving Installments</p>
						<p>Tenant's full moving cost (~€200) split into monthly installments of ~€17 on their Rendin invoice. Rendin pays the mover and recovers the cost over 12 months. Each opted-in cohort keeps compounding as new tenants join each month.</p>
						<div style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(31,35,48,0.08); padding-top: 12px; margin-top: 14px;">
							<span style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); display: block;">€19,380</span>
							<span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted);">collected on the 12th month · 1,140 tenants paying simultaneously</span>
						</div>
						<p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 10px;">1,140 tenants × €17 · Rendin margin ~5–8% net</p>
					</div>
					<div class="cs-card" style="border-top: 3px solid rgba(45, 140, 100, 0.8);">
						<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.68rem; color: rgba(20, 100, 60, 0.85); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 10px;">Option B · Partner Commission</p>
						<p>Moving company pays Rendin ~12% of the booked move value. Avg move = €250. Tenant pays nothing extra — this comes entirely from the partner.</p>
						<div style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(31,35,48,0.08); padding-top: 12px; margin-top: 14px;">
							<span style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); display: block;">€2,850</span>
							<span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted);">/ month · €34k / year</span>
						</div>
						<p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 10px;">95 × €250 × 12% = €2,850</p>
					</div>
					<div class="cs-card" style="border-top: 3px solid rgba(30, 77, 140, 0.7);">
						<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.68rem; color: rgba(20, 55, 120, 0.85); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 10px;">Option C · Placement Fee</p>
						<p>Flat monthly fee paid by 2 vetted moving partners for priority placement in the widget. Not tied to booking volume — predictable regardless of opt-in rate.</p>
						<div style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(31,35,48,0.08); padding-top: 12px; margin-top: 14px;">
							<span style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); display: block;">€600</span>
							<span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted);">/ month · €7.2k / year</span>
						</div>
						<p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 10px;">2 partners × €300/month flat</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="cs-card" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
					<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.09em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 16px;">Why these can stack — they come from different pockets</p>
					<div class="card-grid card-grid-3">
						<div>
							<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--accent-strong); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 6px;">Option A</p>
							<p style="font-size: 0.88rem;"><strong style="color: var(--text);">Tenant pays</strong> the mover's full cost in monthly installments of ~€16–17, added to their Rendin invoice. Rendin pays the mover upfront and recovers the cost gradually. The moving company receives a lump sum from Rendin.</p>
						</div>
						<div>
							<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.68rem; color: rgba(20, 100, 60, 0.85); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 6px;">Option B</p>
							<p style="font-size: 0.88rem;"><strong style="color: var(--text);">Moving company pays</strong> ~€30 referral commission to Rendin after the job is completed. The tenant never sees this. It comes out of the mover's margin, not the tenant's invoice.</p>
						</div>
						<div>
							<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.68rem; color: rgba(20, 55, 120, 0.85); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 6px;">Option C</p>
							<p style="font-size: 0.88rem;"><strong style="color: var(--text);">Moving company pays</strong> a flat €300/month for priority placement — regardless of how many bookings happen that month. Completely independent of booking volume.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(31,35,48,0.08); margin-top: 20px; padding-top: 16px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px;">
						<p style="font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; max-width: 560px;">A and B both flow from the same 95 bookings but are charged to different parties — no double-charging. Option A is a pass-through with a 10% margin; the €125,970 collected across year 1 is not profit — ~€12,600 is. C is independent of bookings entirely.</p>
						<div style="text-align: right; flex-shrink: 0;">
							<span style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); display: block;">~€51k</span>
							<span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.04em;">Rendin net · year 1 · Estonia · A + B + C</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p style="margin-top: 24px;">
					Option C is worth noting as a floor: even if tenant opt-in rates disappoint in month one, Rendin still earns €600/month from partners paying for visibility. A and B scale with bookings; C does not — so the revenue model has a predictable base regardless of early conversion performance.
				</p>

				<div class="callout">
					<p class="callout-label">The Poland multiplier</p>
					<p>Poland's rental market is roughly 10x Estonia's by population, and Rendin has stated it as an expansion priority. The same three-stream model applied to 2,000 contracts/month in Poland projects to <strong>~€180–220k/year</strong> — with near-zero additional build cost, since the feature and partner framework are already in place.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- 04 Solution -->
			<section class="section cs-section panel" id="solution">
				<p class="cs-section-num">04 — Solution & UX Flow</p>
				<h2>What the<br><em>feature looks like</em></h2>

				<p>
					The design principle: <strong>zero extra friction for users who don't want it, high value for those who do.</strong> The feature slots into the existing post-signing experience as a contextual prompt — additive, not disruptive.
				</p>

				<p>
					Rendin should <strong>not</strong> build a moving service. It should build a <strong>curated partner widget</strong> — 2–3 vetted movers, surfaced at the right moment with move-in date and address already filled in from the contract.
				</p>

				<div class="flow-steps" style="margin-top: 36px;">
					<div class="flow-step">
						<div class="flow-num">1</div>
						<div class="flow-body">
							<h4>Agreement signed — the trigger</h4>
							<p>When a tenant signs, Rendin already sends a confirmation email and in-app notification. This is the insertion point. A secondary card: <em>"Your move-in is [date]. Need help moving?"</em> — pulling data Rendin already holds.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="flow-step">
						<div class="flow-num">2</div>
						<div class="flow-body">
							<h4>Mover selection — curated, not open</h4>
							<p>Tenants see 2–3 vetted partners, not a full marketplace. Each shows a rating, price range, and availability for the move-in date. Fewer choices drive higher conversion and create a cleaner incentive for partners to maintain quality.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="flow-step">
						<div class="flow-num accent">3</div>
						<div class="flow-body">
							<h4>Quote request — pre-filled from contract</h4>
							<p>The form is pre-populated with destination address (from contract), move-in date, and apartment size (from listing). The tenant only adds number of boxes and items. This is measurably lower friction than any standalone moving site.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="flow-step">
						<div class="flow-num">4</div>
						<div class="flow-body">
							<h4>Booking — off-platform, tracked</h4>
							<p>Booking happens on the partner's site or via API if supported. Rendin gets a webhook confirmation and logs the referral for commission tracking. No payment infrastructure needed — the referral model keeps this lean.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="flow-step">
						<div class="flow-num">5</div>
						<div class="flow-body">
							<h4>Post-move — handover protocol prompt</h4>
							<p>After the scheduled move-in date, Rendin prompts both parties to complete the digital handover protocol. This closes the loop — the moving feature feeds directly into Rendin's core product and raises protocol completion rates.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="callout" style="margin-top: 0;">
					<p class="callout-label">Brand protection</p>
					<p>Rendin's real risk: if a referred mover damages belongings, trust in Rendin takes the hit. Mitigation: vetting requires insurance, minimum 4.3★ Google rating, and background-checked staff. Rendin's communication is "Rendin Recommended" — not "Rendin Guaranteed." Fast-offboarding clause for any partner with two or more tenant complaints.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- 05 Revenue -->
			<section class="section cs-section panel" id="revenue">
				<p class="cs-section-num">05 — Partnership Model & Revenue</p>
				<h2>Who are the<br><em>right partners</em>?</h2>

				<p>
					The partnership structure should be <strong>exclusive per city, non-exclusive nationally.</strong> Each city gets 1–2 preferred partners, creating a competitive incentive to keep quality high. Rendin never owns trucks.
				</p>

				<table class="partner-table">
					<thead>
						<tr>
							<th>Company</th>
							<th>Base</th>
							<th>Strength</th>
							<th>Fit</th>
							<th>Priority</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td><strong>Moving24.ee</strong></td>
							<td>Tallinn</td>
							<td>5,000+ moves, high-volume ops, English-capable</td>
							<td>Large enough to absorb Rendin referral volume without strain</td>
